tlenecks; Recommended GFF path.\n\n\n**Outlining the GFF Plan**\n\nI'm working on a section detailing how GFF addresses single-tenant VPC deployment challenges, including custom Agent topologies, reusing and filtering from `MOCK_MARKETPLACE_AGENTS`. I'm outlining four proposed workstreams: Infrastructure/VPC Setup, Cognitive Pipeline integration, Agent Topology Orchestration, and Enterprise Handoff. I'm also planning a 90-day roadmap with discovery, OmniMesh integration, and live Supervisor monitoring phases. Finally, I'm specifying a tailored cross-functional squad.\n\n\n**Defining Squads and Measures**\n\nI'm now detailing the cross-functional squad, scaling it by company size, from a two-member team for smaller clients to a larger six-member team for global enterprises, including a cognitive pipeline specialist and a lead verification auditor. I'm focusing on defining the governance approach, which highlights zero-retention policies, telemetry auditing, and air-gapped security. I'm also specifying measurable KPIs for the proposal's success, tailoring the metrics to the client's strategic priorities, such as cost reduction, compliance, speed, customer experience, and automation, and measuring each by percentages or numerical multipliers.\n\n\n**Assessing Potential Risks**\n\nI'm now identifying potential risks and outlining mitigation strategies for this AI proposal, including data complexity, integration friction, and adoption drift. I'm planning to address these with GFF local labs sandboxes, pre-configured OmniMesh connectors, and bi-weekly AI Academy training. I'm also confirming key assumptions, like client-provided infrastructure access keys and legacy database read access.\n\n**Outlining Next Steps**\n\nI'm solidifying the next steps to ensure the proposal's success. This involves a formal architect sync with GFF engineering leads, setting up secure local laboratory sandboxes, and mutually signing final legal and compliance SOW tokens. The plan is to get this into action as soon as possible, once all review is complete.\n\n\n**Implementing Local Storage**\n\nI'm now integrating local storage features. I'll automatically load saved proposal states from `localStorage` under `gff_saved_proposal_inputs`, alongside \"Save Draft\" and \"Reset\" buttons. I'm also adding a function to copy the 11-section outline as plain text, formatted professionally, with a success notification. Finally, I'll add a browser print button and optimize the print layout using `@media print` styles, for a more premium experience.\n\n\n"}}
