{"ts":"2026-06-26T19:53:16.796Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Defining Compilation Flow**\n\nI'm now outlining the interactive compilation flow. First, I'm defining strategic priorities and a budget target. I'll need a \"Live Variable Buffer\" sidebar that updates in real-time, then an elegant \"Sovereign Compile\" button. I anticipate a high-fidelity terminal log animation that resolves after about 1.5 seconds, simulating realistic compilation steps. Finally, I'm planning an interactive document-preview UI, designed to look like a high-end proposal.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-26T19:53:18.572Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Designing Executive Layout**\n\nI'm now focusing on the right-panel strategic canvas, intending to make it feel premium. I'm focusing on an ultra-executive design featuring interactive elements, including an executive summary with custom bold stats, a challenge grid with industry-specific highlights, a dynamic architecture visual, timeline cards for workstreams, and a 90-day roadmap. These sections will trigger a glowing marker on the sidebar as the user scrolls to or activates that section.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-26T19:53:20.379Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Constructing Final Elements**\n\nI'm now focusing on the interactive sections. Specifically, I am planning a card grid of suggested team members, displaying responsibilities and involvement level. I'm also planning a governance approach diagram, including compliance features and remote override protocols. Furthermore, I have gorgeous metric cards for success measures. I'm also going to add clean assumptions, a risk grid, and a next steps action sequence. Finally, I'm thinking about a sticky action toolbar with \"Save Draft Locally\" functionality.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-26T19:53:21.815Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Adding Final Export Features**\n\nI'm now integrating crucial export features for the proposal. I am adding \"Restore Draft\" functionality via a persistent alert/toast. \"Copy Raw Outline\" generates a beautifully formatted markdown dossier with animated visual feedback. \"Browser Print\" invokes `window.print()` with a premium stylesheet. Premium buttons for \"Download PPT Deck\", \"Export PDF\", and \"Export SOW\" will appear as locked features with a subtle tooltip. Finally, I've confirmed and am cross-referencing against the final required sections, including the executive summary, challenge statement, and recommended GFF path.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
