{"ts":"2026-06-26T19:53:28.983Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Defining Proposal Details**\n\nI'm now detailing the specific sections that need to be presented. I envision a premium layout with a large card showcasing key performance indicators for licensing, timeline, security, and priority focus, alongside a narrative summary. I'll need to define content for the challenge statement. This will include both an industry-specific challenge and a data readiness-specific challenge. For example, for a banking application, the challenge will include a discussion of high-latency manual ledger reconciliations, vulnerable public-cloud API integrations, and KYC/AML compliance mandates.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-26T19:53:30.826Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Defining GFF Content**\n\nI'm now diving into the \"Recommended GFF Path\". I plan to define the strategic path structure, incorporating a Garage-Foundry-Factory (GFF) sequence with corresponding week ranges and rationales. I'm also planning to build out the GFF's zero-trust model advantage in relation to public cloud SaaS offerings. The layout will include a high-end architectural block diagram. I'll include the UI and data considerations.\n\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
